Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) Deputy President, Floyd Shivambu, says former Finance minister, Pravin Gordhan, was never eligible for the position. He says he was appointed to the Finance portfolio because he had some exclusive information on former president Jacob Zuma surrounding the “Spy Tapes”. Shivambu says Gordhan was a nobody before he was appointed as the then Minister of Finance. He was addressing EFF members gathered outside the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture, underway in Johannesburg. Watch protest video below:   Watch Commission:  